    "i18nTool.buttons.minimize":  "√Ę‚ā¨‚ÄĚ Minimize",
    "i18nTool.help.body":  "Quick help (top editor bar):\n- √Ę¬¨‚Ä† Import TXT/JSON: loads external translations and merges them into the current project.\n- √Ę‚Äď¬∂ AUTO: starts or pauses automatic batch translation using your current settings.\n- √Ę‚Äį¬° List: hides or shows the left panel (entry list).\n- √ĘŇ°¬° Batch: runs exactly one batch (a single step without the AUTO loop).\n- √įŇł¬ß¬™ Model tests: opens the test dialog and runs the provider/model test.\n- √Ę¬Ě‚Äú: opens this help.\n- √Ę¬¨‚Ä° TXT: exports the full current result to TXT.\n- √Ę¬¨‚Ä° JSON: exports the full current result to JSON.\n- √Ę¬¨‚Ä° Range: exports only the selected G/H number range.\n- √ĘŇ°¬† Failed: lists entries that failed to translate.\n\nRecommended workflow:\n1) Load data with \"√Ę¬¨‚Ä† Import TXT/JSON\" first (if you are continuing previous work).\n2) Use \"√Ę‚Äď¬∂ AUTO\" for continuous runs, or \"√ĘŇ°¬° Batch\" to move forward manually step by step.\n3) Check problems with \"√ĘŇ°¬† Failed\" and re-translate as needed.\n4) Save your work often via \"√Ę¬¨‚Ä° TXT\" or \"√Ę¬¨‚Ä° JSON\".\n5) For a partial export, use \"√Ę¬¨‚Ä° Range\".\n\nNote:\n- \"AUTO\" and \"Batch\" share the same live AI settings (provider, model, batch size, interval).\n- AI pipeline: 1 main model translates; 2 secondary models correct topics and polish the output.",
